OL,6,F"The site had unauthorised gaseous
OL,7,Femissions points and undertook
OL,8,Fmodifications to their process which
OL,9,Fwere not risk assessed or notified to
OL,10,Fthe Environment Agency. The company
OL,11,Fdid not recognise or understand the
OL,12,Fimpact that these changes had on the
OL,13,Fsafety of the plant and failed to take
OL,14,Faction, when warned, which could have
OL,15,Fprevented the incident. These factors,
OL,16,Fand a failure to implement permit to
OL,17,Fwork procedures, including appropriate
OL,18,Frisk assessment, created all the
OL,19,Fnecessary conditions on 20 September
OL,20,F2017 for the explosion which occurred.
